<i> if rehab could delay
 onset of brain disease.</i>

00:09:03.576 --> 00:09:05.711 line:57%
And, you know, my heart--
anyone's heart, I think,

00:09:05.811 --> 00:09:07.747 line:57%
just has to go out
to the athletes.

00:09:07.847 --> 00:09:09.849 line:57%
Because, you know, they put
everything on the line.

00:09:09.949 --> 00:09:11.517 line:57%
And I think,
oftentimes,

00:09:11.617 --> 00:09:13.686 line:71%
they don't even realize what
they're putting on the line

00:09:13.786 --> 00:09:15.855 line:71%
<i> by just playing the
 sport that they love.</i>

00:09:15.955 --> 00:09:18.190 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 While Lewis comes to grips
 with what he can</i>

00:09:18.291 --> 00:09:22.261 line:71%
<i> and can no longer do,
 he is also coming out.</i>

00:09:22.361 --> 00:09:25.898 line:71%
<i> Until now, he has told
 no one of his struggles,</i>

00:09:25.998 --> 00:09:28.668 line:71%
<i> including his own family,
 in Moultrie.</i>

00:09:28.768 --> 00:09:31.537 line:71%
<i> The secret they shouldered
 alone for 15 years</i>

00:09:31.637 --> 00:09:33.906 line:71%
<i> will now be shared.</i>

00:09:34.006 --> 00:09:37.076 line:68%
<i>(Sherry)
His family not knowing,
and us doing this,</i>

00:09:37.176 --> 00:09:39.378 line:71%
<i>has just opened up
another door.</i>

00:09:39.478 --> 00:09:40.846 line:71%
It feels good.

00:09:40.947 --> 00:09:42.181 line:71%
It feels good.

00:09:42.281 --> 00:09:43.916 line:71%
And it feels scary.

00:09:44.016 --> 00:09:46.519 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 Lewis hopes he has
 found a new way forward</i>

