You can't stop.

00:11:56.315 --> 00:11:57.416 line:71%
You can't pause the game.

00:11:57.516 --> 00:11:58.617 line:71%
I don't wanna say
it's addictive,

00:11:58.718 --> 00:11:59.785 line:71%
but it is addictive.

00:11:59.885 --> 00:12:01.687 line:71%
I started to feel like
it was unhealthy, um,

00:12:01.787 --> 00:12:03.389 line:71%
when they started
playing...

00:12:03.489 --> 00:12:04.356 line:71%
Bro, Evan.

00:12:04.457 --> 00:12:06.092 line:71%
... so often that...

00:12:06.192 --> 00:12:07.460 line:71%
Oh, he put a trap down.

00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:09.328 line:71%
... when I called them,
they got irritated.

00:12:09.428 --> 00:12:10.596 line:71%
<i> Shoot the rocket.
 Shoot the rocket.</i>

00:12:10.696 --> 00:12:12.131 line:57%
When they couldn't
pull away from it,

00:12:12.231 --> 00:12:14.333 line:57%
is when I started to
realize it was unhealthy.

00:12:14.433 --> 00:12:17.002 line:57%
Or when their response
to me was disrespectful

00:12:17.103 --> 00:12:20.272 line:57%
as a result of me pulling
them away or interrupting.

00:12:20.372 --> 00:12:23.609 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 It's a slickly-produced,
 intense game of survival.</i>

00:12:23.709 --> 00:12:26.879 line:71%
<i> And currently one of the
 most popular in the</i> country.

00:12:26.979 --> 00:12:29.882 line:71%
<i> Dawn and Jwyanza Watt
 do not allow their boys</i>

00:12:29.982 --> 00:12:32.218 line:71%
<i> any technology during
 the school week,</i>

00:12:32.318 --> 00:12:35.221 line:71%
<i> which can turn weekends
 into free-for-alls.</i>

00:12:35.321 --> 00:12:39.725 line:71%
I think the amount of time
that is consumed is unhealthy.

00:12:41.293 --> 00:12:43.262 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 The World Health
 Organization's definition</i>

00:12:43.362 --> 00:12:45.364 line:71%
<i> of Gaming Disorder
 includes...</i>

00:12:45.464 --> 00:12:47.500 line:71%
<i> behavior that lasts
 for 12 months,</i>

00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:50.069 line:71%
<i> gaming taking precedence
 over other interests</i>

00:12:50.169 --> 00:12:51.804 line:71%
<i> and daily activities,</i>

00:12:51.904 --> 00:12:54.907 line:0%
<i> and playing the game despite
 negative consequences,</i>

00:12:55.007 --> 00:12:57.977 line:0%
<i> whether it's trouble at work,
 school, or at home.</i>

00:12:58.077 --> 00:13:01.981 line:57%
<i> What would your boys choose
 to do over video games?</i>

00:13:02.081 --> 00:13:04.784 line:71%
Sports.

00:13:04.884 --> 00:13:05.918 line:71%
Sports.

00:13:06.018 --> 00:13:06.986 line:64%
Two of 'em, for sure,

00:13:07.086 --> 00:13:10.389 line:57%
would much rather do
sports over video games.

00:13:10.489 --> 00:13:11.357 line:71%
<i> (Jaye)
 Dawn, do you agree?</i>

00:13:11.457 --> 00:13:12.558 line:71%
No.
<i> (laughs)</i>

00:13:12.658 --> 00:13:13.793 line:71%
Why do I keep on
getting hit?

00:13:13.893 --> 00:13:15.294 line:71%
You're on your own, man.

00:13:15.394 --> 00:13:18.197 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 This battle is playing out
 in homes across the country.</i>

00:13:18.297 --> 00:13:19.999 line:71%
<i> A battle of balance.</i>

00:13:20.099 --> 00:13:24.069 line:71%
<i> How to allow gaming without
 it becoming a problem.</i>

00:13:24.170 --> 00:13:26.839 line:71%
It's important
we recognize

00:13:26.939 --> 00:13:28.741 line:71%
people are truly
struggling with this.

00:13:28.841 --> 00:13:30.209 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 Emory Brain Health
 Psychiatrist,</i>

00:13:30.309 --> 00:13:31.477 line:71%
<i> Dr. Justine Welsh,</i>

00:13:31.577 --> 00:13:33.579 line:71%
<i> is an adolescent
 addiction expert.</i>

00:13:33.679 --> 00:13:37.950 line:57%
We actually see, um,
a common thread

00:13:38.050 --> 00:13:41.253 line:57%
between the release of
the chemical, dopamine,

00:13:41.353 --> 00:13:43.055 line:57%
which is largely
responsible

00:13:43.155 --> 00:13:45.925 line:57%
for the sensation of
pleasure and reward

00:13:46.025 --> 00:13:48.694 line:71%
<i>in the same area
of the brain.</i>

00:13:48.794 --> 00:13:51.564 line:71%
And to the same degree
or magnitude, um,

00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:54.166 line:71%
<i>that playing a game has</i>

00:13:54.266 --> 00:13:56.068 line:71%
<i>for someone who may
be addicted to it,</i>

00:13:56.168 --> 00:13:58.404 line:71%
<i>versus using alcohol
and other drugs.</i>

00:13:58.504 --> 00:14:01.841 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 So, gaming is as addictive
 as other addictions?</i>

00:14:01.941 --> 00:14:03.742 line:71%
It can be.

00:14:03.843 --> 00:14:05.244 line:64%
<i> (Jaye)
 As with other addictions,</i>

00:14:05.344 --> 00:14:08.013 line:64%
<i> Dr. Welsh says gamers
 develop a tolerance.</i>

00:14:08.113 --> 00:14:10.216 line:64%
<i> Meaning they need
 to play longer</i>

00:14:10.316 --> 00:14:12.551 line:64%
<i> to get the same
 dopamine reward.</i>

00:14:12.651 --> 00:14:15.120 line:71%
And we also sometimes see
a withdrawal syndrome,

00:14:15.221 --> 00:14:19.058 line:71%
where someone can become
anxious or irritable

00:14:19.158 --> 00:14:20.426 line:71%
when limits are set,

00:14:20.526 --> 00:14:22.494 line:71%
or the games are
actually taken away.

00:14:22.595 --> 00:14:25.931 line:71%
And some of those symptoms
really closely mimic

00:14:26.031 --> 00:14:28.500 line:71%
the symptoms that we see with
substance use disorders.

00:14:28.601 --> 00:14:30.569 line:71%
Yeah!

