<i> that had both carbs
 and fat in them.</i>

00:17:49.902 --> 00:17:51.804 line:71%
So what does it mean?

00:17:51.904 --> 00:17:55.407 line:71%
Well, it is giving us
insight into why we overeat,

00:17:55.507 --> 00:17:58.477 line:71%
and how our craving
for carbs and fat

00:17:58.577 --> 00:18:00.546 line:71%
are making us
overweight.

00:18:02.181 --> 00:18:04.917 line:71%
Our final story is
about expectations.

00:18:05.017 --> 00:18:08.587 line:68%
How they're lowered
when receiving a
devastating diagnosis,

00:18:08.687 --> 00:18:11.990 line:71%
and how they're exceeded
when a passion is discovered.

00:18:12.091 --> 00:18:15.461 line:71%
One so strong that even
a rare genetic disorder

00:18:15.561 --> 00:18:17.529 line:71%
cannot stop it.

00:18:17.629 --> 00:18:19.498 line:71%
Joshua Clark
is his name,

00:18:19.598 --> 00:18:21.366 line:71%
and you won't
soon forget him.

00:18:25.437 --> 00:18:29.508 line:71%
<i> (trumpet playing)</i>

00:18:29.608 --> 00:18:33.612 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 A young man
 playing a trumpet.</i>

00:18:33.712 --> 00:18:37.816 line:71%
<i> It could be a glimpse inside
 a typical suburban home.</i>

00:18:37.916 --> 00:18:41.487 line:71%
<i> But nothing about
 Joshua Clark is typical,</i>

00:18:41.587 --> 00:18:45.157 line:71%
<i> going back to before
 he was even born.</i>

00:18:45.257 --> 00:18:46.992 line:71%
<i>I was laying there,
and the girl said,</i>

00:18:47.092 --> 00:18:49.328 line:64%
"Oh, I see it's a boy.

00:18:49.428 --> 00:18:51.029 line:64%
"We see the little turtle."

00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:52.731 line:64%
And I was like, "What?"

00:18:52.831 --> 00:18:54.299 line:64%
She was like, "Yeah."

00:18:54.399 --> 00:18:57.035 line:64%
And then she went, "Mm."

00:18:57.136 --> 00:18:58.904 line:57%
It was very low.
Like, it wasn't dramatic.

00:18:59.004 --> 00:19:02.674 line:64%
It was like a "Mm.
Mm-hmm."

00:19:02.774 --> 00:19:04.576 line:71%
<i> (Jaye)
 Tuberous sclerosis.</i>

00:19:04.676 --> 00:19:07.646 line:71%
<i> Two words Cheryl Grant
 had never heard.</i>

00:19:07.746 --> 00:19:11.016 line:71%
<i> Two words that would change
 the course of her life,</i>

00:19:11.116 --> 00:19:13.452 line:71%
<i> and that of her son.</i>

00:19:13.552 --> 00:19:16.355 line:57%
Tuberous sclerosis affects
the brain, the eyes,

00:19:16.455 --> 00:19:18.891 line:57%
the lungs, the heart,
the kidneys.

00:19:18.991 --> 00:19:21.260 line:57%
So it's a lot of
different organ systems

00:19:21.360 --> 00:19:22.728 line:64%
that could be affected.

00:19:22.828 --> 00:19:24.096 line:71%
<i> (Jaye)
 The rare genetic disorder</i>

00:19:24.196 --> 00:19:26.965 line:71%
<i> that affects 50,000 people
 in the United States</i>

00:19:27.065 --> 00:19:31.370 line:71%
<i> causes benign tumors,
 and masses called tubers,</i>

00:19:31.470 --> 00:19:34.540 line:71%
<i> to grow in the brain
 and other vital organs.</i>

00:19:34.640 --> 00:19:37.176 line:71%
<i> Joshua's brain
 has many tubers.</i>

00:19:37.276 --> 00:19:41.313 line:71%
<i> But also had a giant
 cell astrocytoma tumor.</i>

00:19:41.413 --> 00:19:44.783 line:71%
<i> A type associated with
 tuberous sclerosis.</i>

00:19:44.883 --> 00:19:48.220 line:71%
So if this is the size of
a five-year-old brain.

00:19:48.320 --> 00:19:50.489 line:71%
The tumor was
half that size.

00:19:50.589 --> 00:19:52.524 line:71%
It was gigantic.

00:19:52.624 --> 00:19:54.993 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 The surgery to remove
 part of that tumor</i>

00:19:55.093 --> 00:19:58.730 line:71%
<i> dramatically impacted the
 left side of Joshua's body,</i>

00:19:58.830 --> 00:20:01.600 line:71%
<i> and his
 cognitive function.</i>

00:20:01.700 --> 00:20:04.736 line:68%
<i> (Cheryl)
 He's probably about along
 the lines of a 15-year-old,</i>

00:20:04.836 --> 00:20:06.605 line:71%
<i> 14, 15-year-old.</i>

00:20:06.705 --> 00:20:08.874 line:71%
Uh, sometimes,

00:20:08.974 --> 00:20:12.277 line:71%
like, if someone
asks me a question,

00:20:12.377 --> 00:20:14.379 line:71%
even if it's a
yes-or-no question,

00:20:14.479 --> 00:20:17.249 line:71%
it'll still take me
a while to answer

00:20:17.349 --> 00:20:20.219 line:71%
because I have
a cognitive delay.

00:20:20.319 --> 00:20:24.957 line:0%
♪♪

00:20:25.057 --> 00:20:26.858 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 Joshua works at
 the cafeteria</i>

00:20:26.959 --> 00:20:28.727 line:71%
<i> of a nearby
 elementary school.</i>

00:20:28.827 --> 00:20:31.063 line:71%
<i> Using the stronger
 half of his body</i>

00:20:31.163 --> 00:20:35.100 line:71%
<i>to compensate for the half
that struggles with basic task.</i>

00:20:35.200 --> 00:20:36.969 line:64%
Biggest thing is,

00:20:37.069 --> 00:20:39.771 line:57%
you have to make sure
that this thing

00:20:39.871 --> 00:20:42.441 line:64%
doesn't become your God.

00:20:42.541 --> 00:20:44.576 line:57%
You will use it as an
excuse for everything,

00:20:44.676 --> 00:20:46.345 line:64%
if you let it.

00:20:47.546 --> 00:20:49.248 line:71%
How are you guys doing?

00:20:49.348 --> 00:20:50.349 line:71%
Doing pretty well.

00:20:50.449 --> 00:20:51.650 line:71%
Mm-hmm.

00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:53.785 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 Emory Neuro Oncologist,
 Dr. Soma Sengupta,</i>

00:20:53.885 --> 00:20:55.954 line:71%
<i> manages Joshua's disorder.</i>

00:20:56.054 --> 00:20:58.824 line:71%
<i> Harsh chemotherapy and
 invasive brain surgeries</i>

00:20:58.924 --> 00:21:01.260 line:71%
<i> have been replaced,
 for the most part,</i>

00:21:01.360 --> 00:21:05.264 line:71%
<i> with drugs that now
 target specific pathways,</i>

00:21:05.364 --> 00:21:07.566 line:71%
<i> keeping the tumors
 in check.</i>

00:21:07.666 --> 00:21:10.002 line:71%
Can you show me
the hand again?

00:21:10.102 --> 00:21:11.803 line:71%
Okay.

00:21:13.805 --> 00:21:17.442 line:71%
It's kinda-- like I said,
it's kinda tense right now.

00:21:17.542 --> 00:21:18.877 line:71%
<i> (Dr. Sengupta)
 Mm-hmm.</i>

00:21:18.977 --> 00:21:20.879 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 Botox helps to
 loosen his hand</i>

00:21:20.979 --> 00:21:23.282 line:71%
<i> in the left side
 of Joshua's body.</i>

00:21:23.382 --> 00:21:25.384 line:71%
<i> But there are many
 tubers in his brain</i>

00:21:25.484 --> 00:21:27.552 line:71%
<i> that cannot be removed.</i>

00:21:27.653 --> 00:21:30.589 line:68%
<i>(Dr. Weinberg)
You have a triangle where
it's just kinda bright,</i>

00:21:30.689 --> 00:21:32.324 line:71%
<i>and brighter
than it should be.</i>

00:21:32.424 --> 00:21:35.594 line:71%
<i>And when that's disrupted,
that's an area of-of injury,</i>

00:21:35.694 --> 00:21:37.663 line:71%
<i>or abnormal tissue there.</i>

00:21:37.763 --> 00:21:39.698 line:71%
<i>And you'll kind of see
other areas throughout,</i>

00:21:39.798 --> 00:21:41.667 line:71%
<i>where they're
scattered throughout.</i>

00:21:41.767 --> 00:21:44.136 line:71%
<i>I mean, it's hard to-to give,
like, an accurate estimate.</i>

00:21:44.236 --> 00:21:46.638 line:71%
<i>But I would say
it's more than 10.</i>

00:21:46.738 --> 00:21:48.907 line:71%
<i>You know, probably many
more than that, even.</i>

00:21:49.007 --> 00:21:51.810 line:57%
Compared to a normal brain,
this is very abnormal.

00:21:51.910 --> 00:21:53.712 line:57%
I mean, there's large
regions of the brain

00:21:53.812 --> 00:21:55.714 line:57%
which are-are
completely different

00:21:55.814 --> 00:21:57.582 line:57%
than they would look
in a normal brain,

00:21:57.683 --> 00:21:59.384 line:57%
in someone
like you or I.

00:21:59.484 --> 00:22:01.486 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 There is an area
 of Joshua's brain</i>

00:22:01.586 --> 00:22:04.189 line:71%
<i> that is interesting
 to his doctors.</i>

00:22:04.289 --> 00:22:08.660 line:71%
<i> It's the part not ravaged by
 surgery and genetic disorders.</i>

00:22:08.760 --> 00:22:11.063 line:68%
<i>(Dr. Weinberg)
Music and language
and auditory processing</i>

00:22:11.163 --> 00:22:14.199 line:71%
<i>are kind of in similar-in
similar parts of the brain.</i>

00:22:14.299 --> 00:22:16.101 line:71%
And, uh, then a lot of
that is done through

00:22:16.201 --> 00:22:18.270 line:71%
the-the lower parts
of the frontal lobe.

00:22:18.370 --> 00:22:19.671 line:71%
So, like, down here,

00:22:19.771 --> 00:22:23.241 line:71%
in which his brain is
relatively normal in that area.

00:22:23.342 --> 00:22:26.345 line:71%
<i> (trumpet playing)</i>

00:22:26.445 --> 00:22:28.413 line:68%
<i>(Cheryl)
The first time
I noticed was, um,</i>

00:22:28.513 --> 00:22:31.817 line:71%
<i>he was in his car seat
and he was humming.</i>

00:22:31.917 --> 00:22:34.319 line:71%
And I was like, I didn't
know babies hummed.

00:22:34.419 --> 00:22:35.887 line:71%
You know?

00:22:35.987 --> 00:22:38.657 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 In a life filled
 with valleys,</i>

00:22:38.757 --> 00:22:43.628 line:71%
<i> this 22-year-old
 has found his peak.</i>

00:22:43.729 --> 00:22:46.331 line:64%
<i> (imitating trumpet playing)</i>

00:23:12.591 --> 00:23:15.160 line:60%
<i> (Jaye)
 Joshua Clark is
 a jazz artist.</i>

00:23:15.260 --> 00:23:18.764 line:71%
<i> With his mouth,
 with his one hand,</i>

00:23:18.864 --> 00:23:21.166 line:71%
<i> with all of himself.</i>

00:23:21.266 --> 00:23:24.403 line:71%
<i> (playing keyboard)</i>

00:23:33.345 --> 00:23:35.247 line:71%
What music does for me,

00:23:35.347 --> 00:23:39.885 line:71%
is it helps me forget
about my frustrations.

00:23:39.985 --> 00:23:42.821 line:71%
I feel kinda
like an outcast.

00:23:42.921 --> 00:23:46.525 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 So does music make you
 not feel like an outcast?</i>

00:23:46.625 --> 00:23:48.326 line:71%
It does.

00:23:48.427 --> 00:23:50.896 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 He wants to bring
 jazz to Millennials.</i>

00:23:50.996 --> 00:23:54.199 line:71%
You know how you're in traffic,
you're at a red light,

00:23:54.299 --> 00:23:55.434 line:71%
and there's that
one person...

00:23:55.534 --> 00:23:59.070 line:71%
<i> (beatboxing)</i>

00:23:59.171 --> 00:24:00.806 line:71%
"Yeah, yeah, yeah",
you know?

00:24:00.906 --> 00:24:02.641 line:71%
Things of that nature.

00:24:02.741 --> 00:24:06.645 line:71%
But, uh, I wanna put
that with jazz music,

00:24:06.745 --> 00:24:08.480 line:71%
to see what it
sounds like.

00:24:08.580 --> 00:24:12.417 line:68%
(Jaye)
His musical ability provides
an unlikely soundtrack

00:24:12.517 --> 00:24:15.720 line:71%
<i> in a life filled with
 love and struggle,</i>

00:24:15.821 --> 00:24:17.522 line:71%
<i> and an unknown future,</i>

00:24:17.622 --> 00:24:20.392 line:71%
<i> where life-shortening
 complications often lurk.</i>

00:24:24.463 --> 00:24:25.797 line:71%
<i> (Cheryl)
 This is like a surprise.</i>

00:24:25.897 --> 00:24:28.200 line:71%
<i> 'Cause you don't know
 what you're unwrapping.</i>

00:24:28.300 --> 00:24:29.768 line:71%
<i> (Jaye)
 In between her two jobs,</i>

00:24:29.868 --> 00:24:32.537 line:71%
<i> Cheryl unpacks boxes
 in their new home.</i>

00:24:32.637 --> 00:24:33.872 line:71%
I love this
picture of you.

00:24:33.972 --> 00:24:36.708 line:71%
Look at that red clay dirt,
down home.

00:24:36.808 --> 00:24:39.077 line:71%
<i> You were so happy.</i>

00:24:39.177 --> 00:24:40.912 line:71%
<i> I wouldn't
 change anything.</i>

00:24:41.012 --> 00:24:42.380 line:71%
It's made me
a better person.

00:24:42.481 --> 00:24:46.151 line:71%
Like, it's made me a more
sober-minded person.

00:24:46.251 --> 00:24:49.154 line:71%
<i> It's made me
 more strategic.</i>

00:24:49.254 --> 00:24:52.023 line:71%
<i> Like, I think more,
 now, globally.</i>

00:24:52.123 --> 00:24:54.993 line:71%
<i> I see the value that
 everybody brings to the table,</i>

00:24:55.093 --> 00:24:56.628 line:71%
<i> now that I have
 this child.</i>

00:24:56.728 --> 00:24:58.697 line:71%
<i> Even my own self worth.</i>

00:24:58.797 --> 00:25:01.733 line:71%
And I think it's
just made me...

00:25:01.833 --> 00:25:04.769 line:71%
just a better person.

00:25:04.870 --> 00:25:07.606 line:71%
<i> He has the best outlook
 of anybody I know,</i>

00:25:07.706 --> 00:25:10.442 line:71%
<i> and does not complain.</i>

00:25:10.542 --> 00:25:12.177 line:0%
And he's-- you know,
I raised him,

00:25:12.277 --> 00:25:13.745 line:0%
but he's so much
better than I am.

00:25:13.845 --> 00:25:14.946 line:0%
And I'm so glad.

00:25:15.046 --> 00:25:16.581 line:0%
<i>(laughing)</i>

00:25:16.681 --> 00:25:19.918 line:0%
He's not near as
petty as I am.

00:25:20.018 --> 00:25:23.855 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 Tuberous sclerosis
 stole a lot of dreams.</i>

00:25:23.955 --> 00:25:27.292 line:71%
<i> His mother says,
 music brought them back.</i>

00:25:27.392 --> 00:25:29.361 line:71%
Oh, I want him happy.

00:25:29.461 --> 00:25:32.697 line:71%
I-- you know, I just picture
him somewhere in France.

00:25:32.797 --> 00:25:35.133 line:71%
Playing music,
and meeting people,

00:25:35.233 --> 00:25:38.036 line:71%
<i> and having a home
 of his own.</i>

00:25:38.136 --> 00:25:40.405 line:68%
<i> (Jaye)
 In a world that has
 not always welcomed him</i>

00:25:40.505 --> 00:25:42.474 line:71%
<i> because of his
 differences,</i>

00:25:42.574 --> 00:25:45.477 line:71%
<i> Joshua does not yearn
 for a different path.</i>

00:25:45.577 --> 00:25:48.813 line:71%
<i> He wants to give back.</i>

00:25:48.914 --> 00:25:53.084 line:0%
I hope that
whatever I attend--

00:25:53.184 --> 00:25:55.520 line:0%
intend to accomplish,

00:25:55.620 --> 00:25:58.023 line:0%
it'd be for not
only for my good,

00:25:58.123 --> 00:26:01.893 line:0%
but for the good of
people besides myself.

00:26:01.993 --> 00:26:02.928 line:0%
You know?

00:26:03.028 --> 00:26:04.996 line:71%
'Cause what-what
good would it do

00:26:05.096 --> 00:26:07.766 line:71%
if it's just benefiting
myself and nobody else?

00:26:09.935 --> 00:26:12.904 line:71%
<i> I'm just glad
 to be living.</i>

00:26:13.004 --> 00:26:16.841 line:71%
<i> It's the little things that
 flourish into big things.</i>

00:26:16.942 --> 00:26:19.010 line:71%
<i> (imitating trumpet playing)</i>

00:26:19.110 --> 00:26:30.021 line:0%
♪♪

00:26:30.121 --> 00:26:32.557 line:71%
Medical interventions
control his tumors,

00:26:32.657 --> 00:26:36.428 line:71%
but Joshua and his mother
also have a positive outlook.

00:26:36.528 --> 00:26:39.397 line:71%
And they have not
had an easy life.

00:26:39.497 --> 00:26:42.400 line:71%
But they're grateful,
even for the hard parts.

00:26:42.500 --> 00:26:45.904 line:71%
A lesson we'd all
do well to remember.

00:26:46.004 --> 00:26:47.539 line:71%
That does it for us
this week.

00:26:47.639 --> 00:26:51.543 line:71%
We'll see you next time,
on "Your Fantastic Mind".

00:26:51.643 --> 00:27:04.789 line:0%
♪♪

